      About this item

      • 4K streaming. Surprisingly big sound. All in one.
      • Perfect for smaller TVs: Enhance your bedrooms or cozy spaces with a 2-in-1 streaming and sound upgrade.
      • Seamless streaming built-in: Enjoy an easy interface with apps that launch in a snapall in brilliant 4K HDR picture optimized for any TV.
      • No closed captions necessary: Hear every word with enhanced speech clarity.
      • Sound upgrade: Elevate your TVs audio with two premium speakers and a dedicated bass port for dynamic tones.
      • Smarter than your average soundbar: Automatically adjust the volume to hear voices more clearly and lower during loud commercials. Try presets for music, movies, and more.
      • Quick guided setup: Everything you need is included in the box. Just plug it into your TV and connect to the internet. Its that simple.
      • No more juggling remotes: Power up your TV, adjust the volume, and control your streaming all with one simple remote.
      • Bluetooth your way: Pair headphones for quiet streaming or play music through your TV sound system.
      • Easily expandable: Add rich depth and booming bass with Roku Wireless Bass subwoofer. Not compatible with Roku Wireless Speakers.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      • Charles Tulumalo
        5.0 out of 5 stars Improved TV sound and functionality in a small package
        Reviewed in the United States on July 7, 2024
        Color: BlackVerified Purchase
        I want to start by giving this 5 stars but with a caveat. It is a five star device as long as you understand that it's not a 5.1 surround sound system and have the appropriate expectations.

        The Roku Streambar SE combines the functionality of a compact soundbar with the added function of a Roku streaming device which is two great things to have in one package.

        First I'll talk about the device itself and some advantages. The device has a compact design that easily blends into any home entertainment setup. It doesnt take up much room below the TV like a 2 foot long sound bar would. It features a couple decent speakers that deliver clear and relatively immersive sound. Compared to just TV speakers, there is a big jump in audio quality of your movies, shows, and music. There is a noticeable amount of bass, mids, and voice clarity. But it's not going to be as good as a larger soundbar with a dedicated subwoofer.

        I love the Roku functionality and that it has 4K, HD, and HDR streaming capabilities versus some of the lower end Roku sticks. You get crisp and vibrant video playback. And all of the apps associated with a Roku device.

        Setting up the Streambar SE is straightforward with Roku's guided setup process. It integrates well with any modern TV, offering a user-friendly interface that allows quick access to a wide range of streaming channels and apps. It's much less complicated than a multi-piece soundbar.

        As a Roku device, the Streambar SE provides access to thousands of channels and streaming services, including popular platforms like Netflix, Hulu, and Disney+. It supports wireless connectivity, allowing you to stream content directly from your smartphone or tablet to the TV screen. This is of course the case for any Roku device.

        The Price is extremely competitive at netween 80 and a 100 bucks. You get a lot of value for anyone looking for an easy upgrade their TV's sound quality while gaining access to a versatile streaming device. I keep stating this but having both in one device is very beneficial.

        Overall, The Roku Streambar SE is an ideal choice for anyone seeking to improve their TV's audio performance and streaming. Itbhas a very compact design, decent enough sound quality, and a great Roku interface. it's a great device that caters to someone looking for a simple upgrade, someone with limited space, or someone that just wants better sound and doesn't need theater surround sound, which is probably a large amount of people.

        A side note. This is a relatively new model. There is a larger model that slots above it if you want to increase the sound quality. You can also add a subwoofer to this for extra cost which would improve the bass response. It's nice to have the flexibility.

      • Chas Grimm
        5.0 out of 5 stars Great for what it is
        Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2025
        Color: BlackVerified Purchase
        Just purchased this to function as monitor speakers for my Mac mini given the airplay functionality. Ill speak to the sound quality and as someone who is also a Roku user that also has its older brother the streambar.

        Sound >> this is a basic, stereo 2 driver soundbar that actually punches above its weight given the size. Do not expect Dolby atmos or virtual surround sound, that is not the intended use case of this product. Its use case is for small TVs/spaces where sound upgrade is needed at a solid price (would only get this when its on sale at $69 or $79).

        Streamer >> similar to the sound functionalities intended audience/use case, this streamer is for relatively niche TVs/monitors that are either (1) old, or (2) too small where all the advanced picture quality features like Dolby vision, HDR 10/+ arent available to begin with. I think the fact the streambar SE comes with 4K HDR is pretty solid in of itself, but others may complain and want more.

        As mentioned above, for my use case as desktop speakers for my Mac mini, this is probably overkill but hey for ~$10 more than comparable dedicated desktop monitor speakers ($40-$60 range vs on sale price of streambar at $69), this seems like a great value imo. Plus, most Mac mini users might use a HomePod mini instead that usually runs $10 more expensive at its on sale price ($79) - I think the streambar SE > HomePod mini for sound purposes.

        Oh, also forgot to mention this streambar has Bluetooth, airplay, chromecast and Spotify connect.

        Overall, this is a value, niche play here for someone who wants to upgrade an old and/or small basic tv that double functions as a streamer+soundbar and doesnt have or need all the Dolby/HDR 10/+ hoopla. And for sub-$70 when on sale, this is a great value.
